{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9406b8b-ecc1-4771-9ba7-28da57c75f81","content":"The project doesn't exist yet in this workspace, but here's how to configure `mcp.json` for a C# MCP server using **stdio** transport:\n\nCreate `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\n        \"run\",\n        \"--project\",\n        \"${workspaceFolder}/src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`dotnet run --project`** — builds and launches your server. For a published binary, replace with the path to the dll/exe.\n- Your server must read JSON-RPC from **stdin** and write responses to **stdout** (no `Console.WriteLine` logging — use **stderr** instead).\n\nIf you've already published the server, use the built output instead:\n\n```json\n\"command\": \"dotnet\",\n\"args\": [\"${workspaceFolder}/src/MyMcpServer/bin/Release/net8.0/MyMcpServer.dll\"]\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2f9a3061-6c44-44b7-a6f6-c2ca5c3d9278","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"B027:100751:D6BA8B:F35272:6A027D40"},"id":"39569b80-85df-4f04-b784-1a76986893c6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:07:19.154Z","parentId":"de6bdbed-a839-4254-a262-ff23202b2ce2"}
